kindred.common

Enum ServerToClientEnum

  • Object
    • Enum<ServerToClientEnum>
      • kindred.common.ServerToClientEnum
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ServerToClientEnum>

    public enum ServerToClientEnum
extends Enum<ServerToClientEnum>
    Contains an enum number for every type of message the Server can send to the Client. Can also encode and decode these values to shorten and simplify Server to Client messages.
    Author:
    Kindred Team

        public static final ServerToClientEnum SUCC_JOIN
        Confirmation that the user has successfully joined the room. The argument is a pipe-separated string containing:

        • order of turns (1 if the player starts, or 2 otherwise)
        • map name

        public static final ServerToClientEnum INFO_SOMEONE_ENTERED_ROOM
